# Modern Chummer 4 — Project Overview

Shadowrun 4th Anniversary Edition web app. Game data comes from legacy ChummerGenSR4 XML converted to JSON.

## Repositories

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `C:\Users\elwin\projects\modern-chummer-4` | Angular 21 app (this project) |
| `C:\Users\elwin\projects\ChummerGenSR4` | Legacy C# Chummer — XML source of truth |

## Key paths

- `public/data/*.json` — converted game data (run `npm run convert`)
- `src/app/core/rules/` — pure TypeScript rules engine (no Angular imports)
- `src/app/core/services/` — Angular data + rules facades
- `tools/xml-to-json/` — XML → JSON converter

## Commands

```bash
npm run convert      # regenerate JSON from ChummerGenSR4
npm run test:rules   # rules engine unit tests (Vitest)
npm start            # dev server at localhost:4200
npm run build        # production build
```

## Implementation phases

1. **Done** — Data pipeline, reference browser, rules engine (Milestones 1–5)
2. **Next** — Per-tab editing (skills, gear, cyberware), career mode

## Legacy reference (when porting rules)

- `ChummerGenSR4/Chummer/clsImprovement.cs` — bonus handlers, `ValueOf`
- `ChummerGenSR4/Chummer/clsCharacter.cs` — derived stats
- `ChummerGenSR4/Chummer/frmCreate.cs` — BP accounting (extract logic, do not port UI)

## Principles

- Reuse Chummer data and rules semantics; do not invent new game mechanics
- Keep formula strings as strings at data layer; evaluate in rules engine
- Item primary key is always `name`
